      "comment": "SOVEREIGN REIGN (1) was safely held in tougher company last start after losing his position early at Wentworth Park, but prior to that won comfortably by 4.5 lengths at Wentworth Park (29.94) beating Call Security in a Grade 5 on April 30. Can atone. PAW LILIBET (2) turned in a moderate run last time when sixth at Wagga over 320m behind Rogue Izmir (18.93) in a Grade 4/5. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Bold showing expected. SANDI KINGDOM (8) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing seventh (20.10) in a Grade 5 at Bulli. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. MADE BY MIA (5) can sneak into the finish.",
